text: It is! A friend finally took a new one for me after 10+ years of my old one :rolling_on_the_floor_laughing:

Tomorrow morning (2/27) at 9AM EST, we will be re-enabling <https://developers.HubSpot.com/changelog/filter-improvements-for-hubl-crm-functions|this change> to how the `eq` filter works in the <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/functions#crm-objects|crm_objects>, <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/functions#crm-object|crm_object>, and <https://developers.HubSpot.com/docs/cms/hubl/functions#crm-associations|crm_associations> HubL functions. tldr, `eq` used to behave like `contains`, and we are updating `eq` to be a true equal comparison, and added support for `contains` for string properties.
The old one was a classic though, hahaha. Great news about the eq filter!
